records.addlTxt:
Defendant Chad L Conrath in court, in custody, with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant was discharged from Drug Treatment Court.  Chris H, Agnes C. and Geri W. make statements on behalf of defendant.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

COUNT 1

2.5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT.  Consecutive to 17CF878 and 15CF869, but concurrent to Milwaukee sentence.  
  -  1 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  1.5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with citizen victims.  May have contact with family victims if family initiates contact.

RESTITUTION:  $77.37 to Capital Bank (to be paid from prison wages and/or to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid from prison wages and/or to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid from prison wages and/or to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
